description: From Old French camphore or Medieval Latin camphora, from Arabic كَافُور‎ (kāfūr), in turn from an Austronesian word such as Malay kapur.

entries.meaning: (organic chemistry) A white transparent waxy crystalline isoprenoid ketone, 1,7,7-trimethylbicyclo[2.2.1]heptan-2-one, with a strong pungent odour, used in pharmacy.
